@a.presse_ latest collection, Fall/Winter 2026 (or “2026 STYLE2”), takes the brand’s familiar approach of recreating rugged vintage Americana through artful and often unexpected materials, but with a noticeably grungier edge. Worn by the shaggy-haired model synonymous with past campaigns, the collection feels darker, shabbier, and more pronounced in its louche scruffiness, from untidy layering and baggy silhouettes to silver wallet chains and dramatic lighting.⁠
⁠
If one look captures the season, it’s a relaxed Type III trucker jacket inspired by Levi’s, cut from a washed silk-cotton blend and styled with a half-unbuttoned check shirt and another tied at the waist. The collection continues A.PRESSE’s signature tension between worn-out Americana and luxurious craftsmanship, pairing purposefully aged sweaters and washed work shirts with delicate fabrics and meticulous construction. For Fall/Winter 2026, that formula remains intact, only now with the grit dialed up even further.⁠

@Charli_XCX annuncia il nuovo album — e il titolo dice già tutto. Music, Fashion, Film arriva il 24 luglio, con i singoli già usciti SS26 e Rock Music. La copertina, fotografata da Aidan Zamiri, mette insieme John Cale, @TheMarcJacobs e Martin Scorsese. Tre universi, una sola immagine. Ci sembra esattamente il tipo di album che non si può ignorare.
